-- Lula Says Brazil to Take Necessary Steps to Guard Against Overvalued Real
-- B y   M a r i a   L u i z a   R a b e l l o
-- 2010-11-03T13:24:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/lula-says-brazil-to-take-necessary-steps-to-guard-against-overvalued-real.html
Brazilian President Luiz Inacio Lula
da Silva said the government will take steps if necessary to
guard against an overvalued real.  Lula, speaking to reporters today in Brasilia, said that
the U.S. and China are engaged in a currency war and that he
plans to take President-elect Dilma Rousseff to the G-20
meetings in Korea.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Luiza Rabello in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 mrabello@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robert Jameson at 
 rjameson@bloomberg.net  